@etimberg or would it be better/preferred to make the sanity check inside the `getLabelCapacity` method?
https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/blob/6f34b2224fd1006a48edd904416ae440cc0a82b5/src/scales/scale.time.js#L751
```javascript
var capacity = Math.floor(innerWidth / tickLabelWidth);
return (capacity && capacity > 0) ? capacity : 1;
```
Edit:
Or should the computed `stepSize` in the `generate` method be sanitized?
https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/blob/6f34b2224fd1006a48edd904416ae440cc0a82b5/src/scales/scale.time.js#L320-L322
```javascript
if (stepSize <= 0) {
    stepSize = 1;
}
```

Another possibility would be to skip the tick creation loop if the `stepSize` is invalid as it would also get rid of the dead-loop due to user misconfiguration.
https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/blob/6f34b2224fd1006a48edd904416ae440cc0a82b5/src/scales/scale.time.js#L349-L351
```javascript
if (stepSize > 0) {
    for (; time < last; time.add(stepSize, minor)) {
        ticks.push(+time);
    }
}
```
